        <num>23-2-57</num>
        <content>
          <p>Fraud may not be presumed but, being in itself subtle, slight circumstances may be sufficient to carry conviction of its existence.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2715; Code 1868, § 2709; Code 1873, § 2751; Code 1882, § 2751; Civil Code 1895, § 4029; Civil Code 1910, § 4626; Code 1933, § 37-706.)</p>
